          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-08 14:57:48" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to recall information from memory, but without necessarily the implication that persons have actually forgotten</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to remember</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to recall</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to think about again</Gloss>
                <Gloss>memory</Gloss>
                <Gloss>remembrance</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages the process of remembering is expressed idiomatically, for example, ‘to find one’s thoughts again’ or ‘to see again in one’s heart’ or ‘to have one’s liver repeat the words.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
