          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-08 14:57:48" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to recall or be aware of information, and as a result to respond in an appropriate manner (for example, punishing, helping, honoring, etc., depending upon the context)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to recall</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to remember</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:04601100200014} the occurrence of μιμνῄσκομαι would seem to imply more than merely a mental state of recalling the presence of Paul in Corinth. The implication may very well be to mentioning Paul in prayer.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
